Diabetes is the fastest growing chronic condition in Australia and all types
Diabetes costs Australia over $14 billion each year and is the leading global
cause of blindness, kidney failure, heart attack, stroke and amputation.
There are 1.2 million Australian living with type 2 diabetes and its estimated
there are a further 500,000 who are undiagnosed. That means there is
approximately 1.7 million Australians either living with diabetes or pre-
Find out if your at risk by completing this quick online assessment. There are
only 12 questions, so five minutes is all the time it should take.
Understanding your risk and taking steps to make simple changes can have a big
impact on your future health and well being.
